article_title: Ohio legislature might avoid voting on keeping Medicaid expansion

article_metadata.description: The much-anticipated debate over whether to continue Gov. John Kasich’s expansion of Medicaid through the next two-year state budget might be over before it starts. Administration sources say they don’t believe lawmakers must reauthorize expansion because it is already in state law and remains so unless it is revoked.
